Interestingly enough, when I close the outline view and re-open it, the outline
is still there. When I hit ctrl-shift-w to close all editors, then the outline
view is emptied.

I'm able to reproduce this in M2 as follows:

1. Start with no editors open
2. Open a java editor
3. Open a class file editor
4. Open another java editor 
5. Shut down eclipse with the last editor active
6. Edit the .classpath file in the workspace to remove everything between
<classpath> and </classpath> (this will force the class file editor to open on a
missing input, which clearly happened in the original scenario)
7. Restart eclipse
8. Close the first editor (the leftmost one -- should be on bottom)
9. Close the top editor (the rightmost one -- should be active)

All editors will disappear, and I get the same "class file", "unhandled
exeption", and "assertation failure" in my log.

Repeating the same steps on M6, and everything works as expected. This appears
to have been caused by the error handling for the PartInitException thrown by
the class file editor, which was fixed by bug 87468



*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 87468 ***
